CONFIRMED genuine skip (#3) — needs the removed Python predefined-named-parameter registration.

gomc removed the embedded Python interpreter. This test's subject is a specific
Python-only extension point: registering *Python-computed predefined named
parameters* (namedparams.py defines _pi, _py_motion_mode, _error, _badreturntype,
which the interpreter exposes as read-only #<_name> params mirroring builtins).

The gomc C interp_ext API (register_oword / register_remap_prolog /
register_remap_epilog) has no equivalent for registering a computed predefined
named parameter, and interp_ctx get_param/set_param only read/write existing
params. So there is nothing to re-express against — this is a genuine removal, not
a transport change. The builtin #<_motion_mode> behaviour the test also touches is
already covered by ordinary NGC interpretation.

Matches the interp/python* and remap/fail/{body-py,canon_error} skips.
